cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.SD, cs.GT. 

This paper deals with the geometric complexity theory program, which is a framework for studying the complexity of computing multivariate polynomials. This makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial and algebraic techniques, which suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as possible sub-categories. The study of Kronecker coefficients and plethysms involves representation theory, which could place the paper in cs.SD (Systems and Control) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
